attributes.name: Sildenafil
attributes.description: Sildenafil contains the same active ingredient as Viagra, but comes at a lower price since you aren't paying for the brand name. It works by establishing a reliable blood flow to the penis, ensuring a strong erection, when you need one.
attributes.long_description:
**How does Sildenafil work?**

By relaxing the blood vessels in your body (and your penis), blood flow is improved and strong, reliable, healthy erections arise. While Sildenafil is not an aphrodisiac, it will help you get or maintain an erection in a situation where you are aroused. In other words, we do the hard work –you take care of the good part.
attributes.summary: Sildenafil contains the same active ingredient as Viagra, but comes at a lower price since you aren't paying for the brand name. It works by establishing a reliable blood flow to the penis, ensuring a strong erection, when you need one.
attributes.availability: Available in packs of 8/16/32 tablets and 25mg, 50mg and 100mg dosage.
attributes.dosage:
A member of our clinical team will decide which dose is right for you following review of your consultation questionnaire. In most cases a 50mg dose is recommended. This can be increased or decreased depending on results and experienced side effect.

If you fall in the below categories, you should not take a dose higher than 25mg.
* You are over 65 years old
* You use potent cytochrome P450
* You have liver failure
* You have a creatine clearance of 30ml/min
attributes.risks:
If you experience any of the following side effects, you may have had an allergic reaction to your medication. Instances of these are rare, but should they occur, please seek immediate medical attention.
* Difficulty breathing
* Dizziness
* Swelling of the face and throat
* Itchiness of the face and throat
* Any rash across your body


Nitrate medications should also be avoided as this combination can produce a severe drop in blood pressure that can cause dizziness, fainting, or even heart attack. Nitrate medications, supplements, and other drugs include the following:
* Glyceryl trinitrate, isosorbide mononitrate and isosorbide dinitrate (used for angina or heart failure – if you experience chest pain after taking Sildenafil DO NOT use nitrates to treat it)
* Nicorandil
* Amyl nitrate 'poppers'

There are also risks in taking Sildenafil if you are taking the following:
* Alpha blockers
* HIV medication
* Cimetidine
* Azole antifungals
* Macrolide antibiotics
* St John’s Wort

Please note that Sildenafil should not be taken in combination with any illegal drugs.

You should always read the dispensing label and the patient information leaflet (PIL) before using any prescription medication.
attributes.side_effects:
When using this medication, you may experience one or more of the following, common Sildenafil side effects:

* Feeling lightheaded or dizzy
* Headaches
* Flushing of the face
* Heartburn
* Indigestion
* Nosebleeds
* Difficulty sleeping
* Swelling of the hands, ankles or feet
* Blurred vision or sensitivity to light
attributes.usage:
When you take Sildenafil, you should:
* Take your prescribed dosage up to 1 hour before having sex. Although depending on your metabolism, it can take between 30 minutes and 4 hours to take effect).
* Swallow the tablet whole.
* Never exceed the daily dose limit.
* Limit alcohol intake to 2-3 units to remain safe.

If you have any of the following conditions Sildenafil may not be the right treatment for you.
* You’ve had a stroke in the last 6 months.
* You have high or low blood pressure.
* You have a heart condition (such as arrhythmia, angina, heart attacks, etc.)
* You have a liver or kidney disease.
* You have fluid in your lungs.
* You have a penile deformity.
* You have sickle cell disease.
* You have painful erections.
